verses.roman:
nityānandera nṛtya,--yena tāṅhāra nartane
upamā dibāra nāhi e-tina bhuvane

synonyms: nityānandera nṛtya—the dancing of Lord Nityānanda Prabhu; yena—as; tāṅhāra nartane—with the dancing of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; upamā dibāra nāhi—there cannot be any comparison; e-tina bhuvane—within these three worlds.
translation: The dancing of Lord Nityānanda Prabhu, like the dancing of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu, cannot be compared to anything within these three worlds.
